#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn17.3"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn17.3:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 17 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 17 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn17.3:0.2"
msgid "1. Paṭhamavagga "
msgstr "1. The First Chapter "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn17.3:0.3"
msgid "3. Kummasutta "
msgstr "3. A Turtle "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.227, sc1
msgctxt "sn17.3:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn17.3:1.2"
msgid "“Dāruṇo, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko … pe … adhigamāya. "
msgstr "“Possessions, honor, and popularity are brutal … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn17.3:1.3"
msgid "Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, aññatarasmiṃ udakarahade mahākummakulaṃ ciranivāsi ahosi. "
msgstr "Once upon a time in a certain lake there was a large family of turtles that had lived there for a long time. "

msgctxt "sn17.3:1.4"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, aññataro kummo aññataraṃ kummaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then one of the turtles said to another, "

msgctxt "sn17.3:1.5"
msgid "‘mā kho tvaṃ, tāta kumma, etaṃ padesaṃ agamāsī’ti. "
msgstr "‘My dear turtle, don’t you go to that place.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn17.3:1.6"
msgid "Agamāsi kho, bhikkhave, so kummo taṃ padesaṃ. "
msgstr "But that turtle did go to that place, "

msgctxt "sn17.3:1.7"
msgid "Tamenaṃ luddo papatāya vijjhi. "
msgstr "and a hunter pierced her with a harpoon. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn17.3:1.8"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, so kummo yena so kummo tenupasaṅkami. "
msgstr "Then that turtle went back to the other turtle. "

msgctxt "sn17.3:1.9"
msgid "Addasā kho, bhikkhave, so kummo taṃ kummaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ. "
msgstr "When the other turtle saw her coming off in the distance, "

msgctxt "sn17.3:1.10"
msgid "Disvāna taṃ kummaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "he said, "

msgctxt "sn17.3:1.11"
msgid "‘kacci tvaṃ, tāta kumma, na taṃ padesaṃ agamāsī’ti? "
msgstr "‘My dear turtle, I hope you didn’t go to that place!’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn17.3:1.12"
msgid "‘Agamāsiṃ khvāhaṃ, tāta kumma, taṃ padesan’ti. "
msgstr "‘I did.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
# NOTE: BB has “struck” both here for upahata and above for vijjhi. In fact vijjhi means “pierced”, i.e. the spear or whatever is stuck in her shell. Upahata is injured.
msgctxt "sn17.3:1.13"
msgid "‘Kacci panāsi, tāta kumma, akkhato anupahato’ti? "
msgstr "‘But my dear turtle, I hope you’re not hurt or injured!’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn17.3:1.14"
msgid "‘Akkhato khomhi, tāta kumma, anupahato, atthi ca me idaṃ suttakaṃ piṭṭhito piṭṭhito anubandhan’ti. "
msgstr "‘I’m not hurt or injured. But this cord keeps dragging behind me.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn17.3:1.15"
msgid "‘Tagghasi, tāta kumma, khato, taggha upahato. "
msgstr "‘Indeed, my dear turtle, you’re hurt and injured! "

msgctxt "sn17.3:1.16"
msgid "Etena hi te, tāta kumma, suttakena pitaro ca pitāmahā ca anayaṃ āpannā byasanaṃ āpannā. "
msgstr "Your father and grandfather met with tragedy and disaster because of such a cord. "

msgctxt "sn17.3:1.17"
msgid "Gaccha dāni tvaṃ, tāta kumma, na dāni tvaṃ amhākan’ti. "
msgstr "Go now, you are no longer one of us.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.228, sc2
msgctxt "sn17.3:2.1"
msgid "Luddoti kho, bhikkhave, mārassetaṃ pāpimato adhivacanaṃ. "
msgstr "‘Hunter’ is a term for Māra the Wicked. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn17.3:2.2"
msgid "Papatāti kho, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasilokassetaṃ adhivacanaṃ. "
msgstr "‘Harpoon’ is a term for possessions, honor, and popularity. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn17.3:2.3"
msgid "Suttakanti kho, bhikkhave, nandīrāgassetaṃ adhivacanaṃ. "
msgstr "‘Cord’ is a term for desire with relishing. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn17.3:2.4"
msgid "Yo hi koci, bhikkhave, bhikkhu uppannaṃ lābhasakkārasilokaṃ assādeti nikāmeti—"
msgstr "Whoever enjoys and likes arisen possessions, honor, and popularity is called a mendicant who has been pierced with a harpoon. They’ve met with tragedy and disaster, and the Wicked One can treat them however he wants. "

#. VAR: bhikkhu giddho papatāya → bhikkhu papatāya (s1-3, km) | bhikkhu viddho papatāya (?)
msgctxt "sn17.3:2.5"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhikkhu giddho papatāya anayaṃ āpanno byasanaṃ āpanno yathākāmakaraṇīyo pāpimato. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn17.3:2.6"
msgid "Evaṃ dāruṇo kho, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko … pe … "
msgstr "So brutal are possessions, honor, and popularity. …” "

msgctxt "sn17.3:2.7"
msgid "evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn17.3:2.8"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

